;;
;; STATUS: parked. The upstream test is built around a single (ns cljs.ns-test
;; ...) form whose :require, :require-macros, and :use clauses pull in JS-host
;; fixture modules (cljs.ns-test.foo, cljs.ns-test.bar, fake.ns, goog,
;; cljs.test) that don't exist in mino. The deftests below all depend on
;; symbols established by that ns form (baz, quux, itsc, always, core-mapv,
;; lang/for, the `+` redef, ::fake/foo). Without it, every deftest is
;; unbound-symbol noise.
;;
;; Re-enable plan: after Phase A lands runtime-namespace :require resolution,
